{
  "texts": [
    "Elise Victor [30] tested the essay-writing capabilities of GPT-3 and 4 and how well these 100% GenAI-written essays would be detected by GenAI detection tools.",
    "The essay written by GPT-3 was flagged as (mostly) GenAI-written by six out of eight detectors, but the essay written by GPT-4 was not flagged to be mostly written by GenAI by any of the detectors.",
    "Moreover, a study on biases in these detection tools by Liang et al. [16] showed that GPT detectors frequently misclassified text from non-native English writers as AI generated.",
    "Even though GenAI detection tools are continuously evolving and improving, it shows that there is an arms race ongoing between the development of better GenAI and better GenAI detection tools.There is a lot of subjectivity and personal beliefs around the debate on whether using GenAI for academic writing is \"good science\", but we can look at the science principles that are widely adopted and accepted as \"good science\", such as the FAIR principles [31].",
    "FAIR stands for Findability, Accessibility, Interoperability, and Reusability."
  ]
}